  "texts": [
    "As Recital 58 states, it balances openness to scrutiny with reasonable confidentiality safeguards, facilitating identification of model deficiencies before broad proliferation.",
    "Furthermore, as Recital 70d of the EU AI Act states [37], provisions enabling scrutiny of opaque AI systems align with DSA risks assessments detecting manipulated content-hence qualified access for examining issues like generative models encoding biases facilitates policy coherence Algorithmic Audits The annual independent DSA audits analyzing VLOPs' algorithmic systems including content curation, recommender processes and advertising auctions (Art.37) offer valuable templates for instituting sustained external oversight assessing influential AI across sectors.",
    "Tailored auditing protocols and benchmarks evaluating aspects like model robustness, representational bias, classification skew, data security, safeguards against misuse, and model limitations mandated through governance measures would be transformative (Code: AD).",
    "The AI Act (Recital 60v) [37] particularly underscores DSA's transparency duties on platforms to mitigate risks from disseminating synthetically generated content-thereby sustained external audits provide oversight regarding risks like generative models propagating information disorders if deployed at-scale.",
    "For instance, the exponential rise of services employing Generative AI e.g."
  ]
